{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/linux/check-cmake-version-in-bash","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>You can check the major and minor numbers of the CMake version installed on your system using the following command in Bash:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token assign-left variable\">CMAKE_VERSION</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span>cmake <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--version</span> <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">grep</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-o</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-P</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-e</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"\\d+\\.\\d+.\\d+\"</span><span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">CMAKE_VERSION_MAJOR</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> $CMAKE_VERSION <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">cut</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-d</span> <span class=\"token string\">\".\"</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-f</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">CMAKE_VERSION_MINOR</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> $CMAKE_VERSION <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">cut</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-d</span> <span class=\"token string\">\".\"</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-f</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">grep</code> options</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">-o</code> is used to print only the matched pattern and not the entire line</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">-P</code> is used to enable Perl-compatible regular expressions</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Should I use \"positive lookbehind assertion\": <code class=\"language-text\">'(?&lt;=cmake version )\\d+\\.\\d+'</code>?</p>","excerpt":"You can check the major and minor numbers of the CMake version installed on your system using the following command in Bash: The  options…","tableOfContents":"","frontmatter":{"date":"May 02, 2022","published":"May 02, 2022","lastModified":"May 02, 2022","title":"Check CMake version in Bash","subtitle":null,"section":null,"draft":null,"developing":null,"buttonText":null,"buttonLink":null,"secondButtonText":null,"secondButtonLink":null,"featuredImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"showLikes":true,"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/linux/check-cmake-version-in-bash.md","url":"/linux/check-cmake-version-in-bash","next":{"excerpt":"If you have two applications and one database in a stack then the  file looks like this Let's say you have an update only in one application…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/linux/how-to-update-only-one-service-in-docker-stack.md","frontmatter":{"title":"How to update only one service","date":"2022-05-09T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"e1769d12-ec53-5db2-8582-0f58c43a4aed"},"previous":{"excerpt":"Fingerprint / thumbprint Serial number Expiration date Convert to Java keystore Verify Code exaples: Java TCP secure server socket","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/linux/ssl-certificates.md","frontmatter":{"title":"SSL Certificates